## API Compatibility Issues

### Issue 1: Login Request Format ❌

**Frontend sends:**
```json
{
  "email": "admin@example.com",
  "password": "password"
}
```

**Backend expects:**
```json
{
  "username": "admin",
  "password": "password"
}
```

**Solution:** Update [Login.tsx](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20new%20updae%202.0/ldm_test/src/pages/Login.tsx) to send `username` instead of `email`

---

### Issue 2: Login Response Format ⚠️

**Backend returns:**
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "token": "eyJ0eXAi...",
  "user": {
    "id": "1",
    "username": "admin",
    "name": "Admin User",
    "email": "admin@example.com",
    "role": "Admin"
  }
}
```

**Frontend expects:** (from Login.tsx line 28)
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "user": {
    "id": 1,
    "username": "admin",
    "role": "admin",  // lowercase
    "...": "..."
  }
}
```

**Issues:**
1. Backend sends `token` at root level, frontend expects it in `data.token`
2. Backend role might be "Admin" (capitalized)
3. Frontend needs token stored but Login.tsx doesn't handle it

**Solution:** Update Login.tsx to:
- Store token in localStorage
- Handle role case sensitivity

---

### Issue 3: Auth Check Response ⚠️

**Backend `/api/auth/check` returns:**
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "valid": true,
    "user": { "..." }
  }
}
```

**Frontend expects:** (AuthContext.tsx line 40)
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "isAuthenticated": true,
  "user": { "..." }
}
```

**Solution:** Update AuthContext to check `data.valid` instead of `isAuthenticated`

---

## Required Frontend Fixes

### Fix 1: Login.tsx - Use username instead of email

**File:** [ldm_test/src/pages/Login.tsx](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20new%20updae%202.0/ldm_test/src/pages/Login.tsx)

**Change line 7:**
```typescript
// From:
const [email, setEmail] = useState('');

// To:
const [username, setUsername] = useState('');
```

**Change line 23:**
```typescript
// From:
body: JSON.stringify({ email, password }),

// To:
body: JSON.stringify({ username, password }),
```

**Change line 28-29 (add token storage):**
```typescript
if (data.success) {
    // Store token
    localStorage.setItem('authToken', data.token);
    localStorage.setItem('userRole', data.user.role.toLowerCase());
    
    login(data.user);
    // ... rest of code
}
```

---

### Fix 2: AuthContext.tsx - Fix auth check response

**File:** [ldm_test/src/context/AuthContext.tsx](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20new%20updae%202.0/ldm_test/src/context/AuthContext.tsx)

**Change line 40:**
```typescript
// From:
if (data.success && data.isAuthenticated) {

// To:
if (data.success && data.data?.valid) {
    setUser(data.data.user);
```

